Adaboost and Gradient Boosting Training

Nguyen Hai Truong & Nguyen Minh Thanh

May 22, 2017

1 L thuyt

1.1 So snh vi Bagging

Bagging dng bootstrap ly ngu nhin cc tp con t tp train ban u, sau xy dng cy quyt nh vi mi tp con (cc cy hon ton c lp vi nhau), ri kt hp tt c cc cy li to ra 1 m hnh d bo (bng cch ly trung bnh hoc bnh chn theo s ng cc kt qu d bo t cc cy quyt nh ni trn).

Boosting hot ng theo cch tng t, tr vic cc cy quyt nh c xy dng sequentially: Mi cy k tip c xy dng bng cch s dng kt qu t nhng cy trc . Boosting tp trung nhiu hn vo nhng quan st b d bo sai t nhng cy trc gp phn ci thin cht lng d bo ca m hnh cui cng. Boosting khng dng bootstrap sampling, m thay vo l vic dng modified version ca tp train ban u.

1.2 Cc thut ton Boosting

Mt s loi thut ton Boosting tiu biu:

  • AdaBoost (Adaptive Boosting)

  • Gradient Boosting

  • XGBoost (Extreme Gradient Boosting)

1.2.1 AdaBoost

AdaBoost kt hp cc cy phn loi yu to thnh cy phn loi mnh (cy phn loi yu l cy phn loi tt hn 1 cht so vi random guessing). Sau mi bc lp, nhng quan st b phn loi sai s c nh trng s cao hn, nhng quan st c phn loi ng s nh trng s thp hn. Mi cy tip theo c xy dng vi mc tiu phn loi ng nhng quan st b phn loi sai cy trc .

1.2.1.1 V d

Din gii:

  • Box 1: nh trng s bng nhau i vi tt c quan st v build mt decision stump - D1 (cy ch gm 1 split) phn loi cc quan st thnh 2 nhm + v -. Kt qu cho thy c 3 quan st b phn loi sai (l + nhng li b cho vo nhm -), 3 quan st ny s c nh trng s cao hn v tip tc build decision stump khc - D2.

  • Box 2: D2 c build vi mc ch phn loi ng 3 quan st b phn loi sai D1. Kt qu cho thy, li c 3 quan st b phn loi sai (l - nhng b cho vo nhm +). Li tip tc nh trng s cao hn i vi nhng quan st ny v tip tc build decision stump - D3.

  • Box 3: D3 c build vi mc ch phn loi ng 3 quan st b phn loi sai D2. Kt qu cho thy vn c nhng quan st b phn loi sai.

  • Box 4: Kt hp D1, D2, D3 to thnh D4 - phn loi tt hn so vi D1, D2, D3 (nhm + v - c phn loi hon ton).

1.2.1.2 Algorithm

1.2.2 Gradient Boosting

Gradient Boosting = Gradient Descent + Boosting

C AdaBoost v Gradient Boosting u kt hp cc weak learner to thnh mt strong learner v u tp trung vo nhng quan st b d bo sai. AdaBoost th nh trong s cao hn vo nhng quan st b d bo sai ti mi cy trc, v c gng d bo ng nhng quan st ti cy tip theo. Trong khi , vi Gradient Boosting, mi mt cy mi s c xy dng vi mc tiu minimizes dn tng loss ca cy trc bng vic s dng phng php gradient descent.

Trong Gradient Boosting, vic tnh tng loss da vo vic la chn loi loss function no, v d nh: square loss, absolute loss, huber loss. Mi loi u c nhng u/nhc im ring.

Square loss:

\[L(y,F) = (y-F)^2/2\]

Absolute loss:

\[L(y,F) = |y-F|\]

Huber loss:

\[\begin{cases}(y-F)^2/2 & |x-F| \leqslant \delta\\\delta(|y-F| - \delta/2) & |x-F| > \delta\end{cases}\]

V d:

1.2.2.1 Algoritm

1.3 Tuning parameters

  • S lng cy (B): Khng ging nh Bagging & Random forests, Boosting c th b overfitting nu nh B qu ln. Chng ta s dng cross-validation la chn B.

  • The shrinkage parameter/learning rate ( > 0): gi tr mc nh thng l 0.001. Nu chn qu nh th s yu cu gi tr B rt ln t c cht lng m hnh tt.

  • Interaction depth (d): limits depth of each tree - s tng/splits ca mi cy.

2 Thc hnh vi R

2.1 Data

S dng data \(GermanCredit\)

y l data ghi nhn v lch s vay ca khch hng, vi cc 61 bin cng vi bin Class ghi nhn thc t l cc khon vay c phi l khon n xu hay khng.

rm(list = ls())
data("GermanCredit")
data <- GermanCredit
rm(GermanCredit)
#Function cho tnh ton ch s m hnh
model.performance <- function(confusion_matrix) {
  a <- confusion_matrix[1,1]
  b <- confusion_matrix[1,2]
  c <- confusion_matrix[2,2]
  d <- confusion_matrix[2,1]
  
  tpr <- c/(b+c)
  precision <- c/(c+d)
  accuracy <- (a+c)/(a+b+c+d)
  
  print(paste('tpr :',round(tpr,2)))
  print(paste('precision :', round(precision,2)))
  print(paste('accuracy :',round(accuracy,2)))
  }
#Chia data
set.seed(123) 
indxTrain <- createDataPartition(y = data$Class,p = 8/10,list = FALSE) 
training <- data[indxTrain,] 
testing <- data[-indxTrain,] 

df.train <- training
df.train$Status[df.train$Class == "Good"] <- 1
df.train$Status[df.train$Class == "Bad"] <- 0


df.test <- testing
df.test$Status[df.test$Class == "Good"] <- 1
df.test$Status[df.test$Class == "Bad"] <- 0

  • Learning rate: 0.01

  • S tng ca cy: 4

#Gradient Boosting

                 data = df.train,

2.4 p dng 2 m hnh vo bi ton kinh t

Gi s mi khch hng vay 100USD, mi khch hng d bo l tt s mang li 10% li nhun tc 10USD cn vi mi khch hng n xu s mt ton b s tin cho vay. Ta cn so snh li ch kinh t ca 2 m hnh

2.4.1 Li nhun t m hnh Adaboost

table <- seq(0.11,0.98,0.01)
table <- table %>% as.data.frame()
names(table)[1] <- "cutoff"
for (i in seq(0.11,0.99,0.01)){
  ada.result
  ada.conf  <-  rep ("Bad", 200) 
  ada.conf[ada.result >= i] = "Good" 
  confusion <- table(ada.conf, df.test$Class)
  
  profit <- confusion[2,2]*10- confusion[2,1]*100
  cutoff <- i
  
  df <- cbind(cutoff, profit)
  df <- df %>% as.data.frame()
  
  table$benefit[table$cutoff %in% df$cutoff] <- df$profit
}

2.4.2 Li nhun t m hnh Gradient Boosting

table1 <- seq(0.13,0.98,0.01)
table1 <- table1 %>% as.data.frame()
names(table1)[1] <- "cutoff"
for (i in seq(0.13,0.98,0.01)){
  gbm.result
  gbm.conf  <-  rep ("Bad", 200) 
  gbm.conf[gbm.result > i] = "Good" 
  gbm.confusion <- table(gbm.conf, df.test$Class)
  
  profit <- gbm.confusion[2,2]*10- gbm.confusion[2,1]*100
  cutoff <- i
  
  df <- cbind(cutoff, profit)
  df <- df %>% as.data.frame()
  
  table1$benefit[table1$cutoff %in% df$cutoff] <- df$profit
}
